# WHAT IT IS
#   Draw Things (drawthings.ai) is a privacy-first on-device
#   Stable Diffusion application available on macOS, iPadOS, and
#   iPhone.  Built by Liu Liu (formerly of Snap Inc.; original
#   author of the Caffe-like deep-learning framework `nnc`), it
#   has become the **dominant local image-generation app on Apple
#   platforms** (3M+ downloads, top of the Mac App Store
#   Photography category since 2023).  Unlike browser-based or
#   cloud-hosted alternatives (DALL-E, Midjourney, Stability AI
#   API, Replicate), Draw Things runs every model on-device using
#   Apple Neural Engine + Metal Performance Shaders for native
#   Apple Silicon performance with no data leaving the device.
#
#   In version 1.20240326.0 (early 2026), Draw Things shipped a
#   `gRPCImageGenerationService` server mode — invoking `Draw
#   Things.app` with the `--grpc` command-line flag exposes the
#   full Image Generation pipeline as a gRPC service on
#   `localhost:7859`.  This lets external tools (AI coding
#   agents, scripting workflows, automated content pipelines)
#   generate images without driving the Draw Things GUI.
#
#   `dt-skill` is the canonical command-line client for that
#   gRPC endpoint.  Two flavors of bin ship from the same npm
#   package:
#
#     1. **`dt-skill`** — a commander.js-based CLI that AI coding
#        agents (Claude Code's Skill subsystem, OpenCode's tool
#        registry, OpenClaw, Gemini CLI) can register as a Skill
#        / Tool / Command for in-conversation image generation.
#        Subcommands:
#          gen     — generate an image from a text prompt
#          config  — manage skill config (server path, models
#                    dir, server address, TLS)
#          doctor  — verify paths + server status
#          models  — list available models + upscalers
#          server  — start/stop/restart/status the gRPC server
#
#     2. **`dt-mcp`** — a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server
#        that exposes the same surface to MCP-aware clients
#        (Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cline, Continue.dev,
#        every modern AI coding agent that speaks the MCP
#        protocol).  MCP is Anthropic's open standard for
#        connecting LLMs to external tools / data sources.
#
#   The wire protocol between dt-skill and Draw Things.app is
#   the typed `imageService.proto` proto-buffer service
#   definition that ships in the npm package's `scripts/`
#   directory, loaded at runtime via @grpc/proto-loader's
#   typed `loadSync` API and converted into a typed
#   `ImageGenerationService` gRPC stub via @grpc/grpc-js's
#   typed `grpc.loadPackageDefinition` typed loader.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from scripts/cli.js
#                       commander.js subcommand registrations;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of scripts/cli.js)
#
#   dt-skill <COMMAND> [ARGS...]
#
#   Commands:
#     gen [OPTIONS]                  Generate an image from a
#                                    text prompt
#         --prompt <TEXT>            Text prompt for image
#                                    generation
#         --negative-prompt <TEXT>   Negative prompt to exclude
#                                    elements
#         --width <N>                Image width
#                                    [default: 1024]
#         --height <N>               Image height
#                                    [default: 576]
#         --steps <N>                Number of sampling steps
#                                    [default: 8]
#         --seed <N>                 Random seed (0 for random)
#                                    [default: 0]
#         --guidance <F>             Guidance scale
#                                    [default: 1.0]
#         --sampler <NAME>           Sampler name
#                                    [default: unicpc-trailing]
#         --model <FILENAME>         Model filename
#                                    [default:
#                                     z_image_turbo_1.0_q6p.ckpt]
#         --lora <NAME:WEIGHT>       Add LoRA (e.g. style:0.8;
#                                    repeatable)
#         --upscale <FACTOR>         Upscale factor (e.g. 2, 4)
#                                    [default: 1]
#         --output <PATH>            Output image path
#         --image <PATH>             Input image for Img2Img
#         --strength <F>             Denoising strength for
#                                    Img2Img (0.0-1.0)
#                                    [default: 0.7]
#     config [OPTIONS]               Manage skill configuration
#         --server-path <PATH>       Path to Draw Things gRPC
#                                    server binary
#         --models-path <PATH>       Path to models directory
#         --addr <HOST:PORT>         gRPC server address
#                                    [default: localhost:7859]
#         --tls <BOOL>               Enable/Disable TLS
#                                    [default: true]
#         --show                     Show current configuration
#     doctor                         Run diagnostics to verify
#                                    paths and server status
#     models                         List available models +
#                                    upscalers
#     server <SUBCOMMAND>            Manage the Draw Things
#                                    gRPC server process
#         start                      Start the server in
#                                    background
#         stop                       Stop the running server
#         restart                    Restart the server (apply
#                                    configuration changes)
#         status                     Check if the server is
#                                    healthy and responsive
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version (1.0.0)
#
#   `dt-mcp` exposes the same surface as a Model Context
#   Protocol server (no CLI flags — runs on stdio and
#   communicates via the MCP JSON-RPC protocol with the calling
#   AI agent).
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `mijuu/drawthings-agent` declares **direct** dependencies on
#   `@grpc/grpc-js@^1.12.6` AND `@grpc/proto-loader` in its
#   `package.json` (verified via npm-registry inspection of
